way of life he was just he was you know dressing nicely holding his ball his bowl beautifully saying the right things always looking monkish and spiritual and uh when he woke up to that he he left you know he just he'd been play acting although i dare say his original impulse uh to his original um desire to become a monk had been real but that really uh sort of undermined him

184
00:23:16,251 --> 00:23:44,115
so eventually i think uh it's this whole thing about distinguishing between what is a beneficial self-criticism um you know to be able to think to be able to look at one's actions and recognize that they're not wholesome they're not they're not good and then to make that determination uh not to behave like that um we can be a bit too sensitive we can be a bit too lax with our behavior

185
00:23:44,855 --> 00:23:53,663
But we learn that just through doing what we think is correct and then learning from those mistakes.

